gameData.hints: I sleep and give birth standing up.
I secrete milk from my skin.
I can eat up to one third of my body weight in food. Keep me away from buffets.
Humans often use me to reduce mosquito populations.
My eyes can move in two different directions at the same time. It's a cool party trick.
My color is the result of what I eat.
I am a surprisingly very fast runner.
Males of my species die when they mate.
I only sweat through pads on my feet. Too bad there's not deoderant for feet.
The ancient Romans used me to pull chariots.
I can be over 10 feet tall when I stand on my hind legs.
I can find my babies among thousands of others by their unique voices and scents.
We can communicate with each other before we even hatch.
Some of us like to dance to music.
I bleed from my knees when threatened.
Between 30 and 80 percent of my flesh is made of water.

prey: squid and other forms of sealife
gameData.hints: Even though I don't have visible ears, I have excellent hearing.
diet: squid and other forms of sealife

gameData.hints: My kind are very playful and compassionate, even to you humans.

habitat: the abyssal depths of the sea
gameData.hints: Our courtship rituals last between 2 and 12 hours.
Our eyes are not technically considered 'eyeballs.'
specialinfo: can turn head all the way around

gameData.hints: I have a bandit's mask which has unfortunately given me a reputation for mischief.
I can live entirely on land or entirely in the water, depending on my species.
I exist on every continent besides Antarctica.
My gender depends on how hot or cold the environment was when I was in my egg.
You're not going to want to step on me. Seriously.
Our kind remain monogamous our entire lives.
I have taste receptors on my feet. I love standing on cake or something tasty.
You can hear my roar as far as 3 kilometers away, or approximately 1.86 miles.
I can't chew my food, so I inject digestive juices into my prey and wait for them to turn into a juice. Just normal eating stuff.
I'm blind when I'm born, but I can open my eyes two weeks after my birth.
I'm red-green colorblind.
I have bigger eyes than any other mammal that lives on land.
You might be surprised to know that I can be trained to use a litterbox, walk on a leash, and do tricks.
My back is very flexible because I have up to 53 loosely fitting vertebrae.
I spend 16 to 20 hours a day sleeping or resting.
A snake bite cannot kill me because I am immune to snake venom.
I have thumbs that allow me to grasp bamboo stalks.
I am afraid of water and will cross streams only if I can do so without getting wet.
I can cover 15 feet in a single hop.
I form deep bonds with my family. I love you, mom and dad.
